            }, 
            {
                "margin":[0,0,0,0],
                "style":"pdfContent", 
                "text":"All this calculation is subject to post-audit."
            },
            {
                "margin":[0,10,0,0],
                "style":"pdfContent", 
                "preserveLeadingSpaces": true,
                "text":"            The firm was directed number of times to clear the dues during hearing of case but the firm has not cleared the dues inspite of sufficient opportunities given by the court."      
            },
            {
                "margin":[0,10,0,0],
                "style":"pdfContent", 
                "preserveLeadingSpaces": true,
                "text":"            Keeping in view of the facts, the undersigned is of the view that firm is not paying attention to clear the outstanding dues. The undersigned is convinced that firm is not serious about payment of dues and therefore ! have left with no other alternative but to cancel the allotment/lease of M/s Lok Priya Buildwell Pvt. Ltd., Hotel Site Block No. 6, Sector 35-B, Chandigarh measuring 12694.422 sq yd. (approx.) on account of non payment of outstanding dues of Rs.7,81,29,024/- as on 10.11.2017. Therefore, I, Uma Shankar Gupta, PCS, Additional Commissioner-cum Estate Officer, Municipal Corporation, Chandigarh exercising the powers of the Estate Officer under the provisions of Capital of Punjab (Development & Regulation) Act, 1952 hereby cancel the allotment/lease of M/s Lok Priya Buildwell Pvt Ltd. Hotel Site Block No. 6, Sector 35-B, Chandigarh measuring 12694.422 sq yd. (approx.) with immediate effect as per condition No. 22 of the terms and conditions of allotment letter and further order to forfeit 10% of the premium, ground rent, interest and other dues to be calculated as per rule 14 of Chandigarh Estate Rules, 2007 read with Section 8-A of the Capital of Punjab (Development and Regulation) Act, 1952 as amended from time to time. I, further order to lodge eviction complaint with SDM-cum-Estate Officer (Under Public Premises) Act, 1971 against all unauthorized occupants for eviction from the public premise in question and for recovery of outstanding amount alongwith interest and penalty as applicable till the date of final realization through Collector, U.T., Chandigarh as arrears of Land Revenue."      
            },
            {
                "margin":[0,10,0,0],
                "style":"pdfContent", 
                "preserveLeadingSpaces": true,
                "text":"            Announced on 10.11.2017. issued under my hand and seal on this 10th day of November, 2017."      
